WHAT THIS PROJECT ACTUALLY IS

This is not primarily an AI governance tool, though it is that. It is not primarily a multi-model orchestration framework, though it is that too. It is a complete rethinking of how AI systems relate to people, knowledge, and accountability — built from the infrastructure up rather than bolted on after.

Three problems are being solved simultaneously:

**Problem 1 — AI systems have no accountability.** When an AI makes a consequential decision — medical, financial, legal, operational — there is no mechanism to reconstruct what it knew, what it was authorized to do, or why it said what it said. Regulators are demanding this. Nobody has built it.

**Problem 2 — AI systems surveil rather than serve.** Current AI assistants know things about you because they watched you. You have no control over what they know, no ability to correct it, no visibility into how it's used. This is surveillance capitalism with a chat interface.

**Problem 3 — Knowledge creators are not compensated when AI uses their work.** Publishers, doctors, engineers, educators publish authoritative content. AI systems train on it or retrieve it. Nobody gets paid. Nobody gets credited. The knowledge economy is broken.

The Hydra Kernel architecture solves all three structurally, not through policy or promises.

