THE THREE DEPLOYMENT SCENARIOS

These scenarios are the README that doesn't exist yet. They are the thing that makes someone understand in 90 seconds why this matters.

Scenario 1 — The Developer (Vibe Coder)

You are iterating a software project through conversation with an AI. Every session you re-explain your coding style, your project context, your conventions, what the AI tried last time that didn't work. You lose context constantly. When the AI drifts from your intent you have no way to detect or correct it.

Vibe Coder makes your coding context a versioned, encrypted knowledge base. You inject it at the start of any session on any platform — Claude, GPT, Gemini, doesn't matter. You commit code checkpoints with messages. You branch for experiments. You roll back when something breaks. The AI stays in your context rather than its training data defaults. The drift detector tells you when it's wandering. This is git for the way you actually work with AI.

Scenario 2 — The Consumer (AI Space)

You want to buy running shoes. Your AI Space knows you pronate, prefer purple, never spend more than $100, and won't shop at Payless. You ask. You get options that respect all four constraints simultaneously — not because the AI guessed or the advertiser paid to interrupt you, but because you told it.

You want to cook dinner. Your AI Space knows you like peanut butter, are allergic to eggs, and your stove is broken but you have an air fryer. The recipe it suggests accounts for all of this without you explaining it again.

Your car needs an oil change in the next few weeks. You tell your AI to keep an eye out for sales. It holds that as background intent and surfaces it when conditions are right. You didn't search. You didn't get interrupted by an ad. You got a relevant suggestion at the right moment because you asked for it.

When the AI gets it wrong — recommends an orange wide-toe Payless shoe with no pronation support — you can look at the DRE output and see exactly why: which constraints it weighted incorrectly, what knowledge it was working from. You correct the Persona Vector. It doesn't happen again.

**This inverts surveillance capitalism structurally.** The advertiser doesn't pay to interrupt you with a guess about what you want. The advertiser pays to be findable when you are actually looking for what they sell. Your intent is the connector, not your behavioral profile harvested without consent.

Scenario 3 — The Humanitarian (Expert in a Box)

A ruggedized tablet in a remote village runs an Expert Pack — educational content, basic medical guidance, local agricultural knowledge — fully offline. A student uses it as a tutor for six months. The system learns their level, their learning style, their language.

A hurricane hits. The emergency VCKB pack activates — pre-loaded, offline-capable, signed by medical authorities. The system knows this specific person's knowledge level and calibrates its instructions to what they can actually execute under acute stress, not to a hypothetical average person.

Someone brings a casualty with a severe leg injury. A telemetry device goes on the victim. The system reads vital signs in real time and provides triage guidance calibrated to both the responder's training level and the victim's actual physiological state. The DRE records every instruction given, every telemetry reading, every decision — so when the casualty finally reaches a surgeon, the surgeon receives a complete chain-of-custody record, not a panicked bystander's fragmentary memory.

The same architecture, the same governance primitives, deployed at the human scale in the place that needs it most.

**The dongle is the DLC made physical.** A person who cannot afford a phone or a data plan carries their AI Space on a USB dongle. They plug into any available surface — a kiosk in Mumbai, a library terminal, a borrowed laptop. The kiosk isn't their AI. The kiosk is a screen and a processor. Their AI Space — their context, their entitlements, their governed personal knowledge — travels with them. Expert in a Box at a kiosk, with a dongle, is the Mumbai deployment of the same infrastructure that handles enterprise AI governance.

