THE APP PIPELINE — WHAT IT IS AND IS NOT

Applied Pattern Physics is a cross-domain reasoning framework. The APP Pipeline applies it as a multi-model reasoning process:

Problem submitted
→ FM1 (Frontier Model) maps the substrate: what is the medium, what patterns recur, what keeps them stable, what would the desired stable state look like
→ SLMs (parallel, cheap) each propose ONE structural constraint modification — not a solution, a change to the conditions
→ FM2 scores each candidate against APP principles, blind to which SLM generated what
→ Adversarial Lane simultaneously tries to falsify FM1's substrate analysis (red-team)
→ Arbitration filters convergent candidates (echo chamber warning), contradictory candidates
→ Human reviews ranked shortlist — ACCEPT, REJECT, MODIFY, DEFER
→ Pattern Library records all decisions as ground truth

**APP is a governed demonstrator, not the constitutional anchor.** The Constitutional Outline V2.0 makes this explicit. The Hydra / VCKB / DLC architecture stands independently of APP. APP is useful because it exercises the full three-pillar architecture and produces outputs that are structurally different from a well-prompted frontier model — not because the AI is smarter but because it's directed to search a different part of the solution space.

The demo target: same problem, standard AI answer vs APP pipeline answer, side by side. If the pipeline answer surprises the person who submitted the problem, the system is working. The outputs may be genuinely novel or completely absurd — either serves the purpose of demonstrating the governed pipeline and getting people to look at the AI governance middleware that produced it.

**The claim of novelty is still unproven.** FM1 and minimal SLM generation are now live in code, but scoring, review, and pattern-library update remain unfinished. This is the honest status.

