V3.0 ADDITIONS — 2026-03-23

MULTI-PIN DLC — HOW IT ACTUALLY WORKS

The DLC token is assembled from three independently encrypted components. Each component has its own PIN. This is not one password that unlocks everything — it is three (or more) separate unlock events that all must succeed.

**The PIN structure:**
•	Your personal PIN: unlocks the Personal Signature component
•	One model PIN per AI you use: Claude gets its own PIN, GPT gets its own, Gemini gets its own
•	One entity PIN per organization you operate under: work, lodge, association, etc.

**The paranoia compound effect:**
Security = f(PIN_length, PIN_count). An attacker needs ALL component PINs. They also don't know which entities you have — they don't know if you have a lodge PIN or not. Longer PINs resist brute force. More entity PINs resist social engineering. Both axes together resist everything.

**What gets stored on disk:**
Encrypted blobs only. `~/.hydra/dlc_personal.enc`, `~/.hydra/dlc_model_claude.enc`, `~/.hydra/dlc_entity_work.enc` etc. Each is `{salt, iv, encryptedBlob}`. The PIN is never written anywhere. The decrypted component exists only in memory during token assembly. The assembled token exists in memory for its TTL, then is zeroed.

**Invariants this enforces:**
•	Invariant 12: No ambient access — token must be actively assembled with correct PINs
•	Invariant 15 (NEW): DLC assembled in memory only, never written to disk
•	Invariant 16 (NEW): PINs never stored, discarded immediately after key derivation

