What You're Seeing

When you run the APP pipeline test, the GEL:
1. Intercepts the request through the governance plane
2. Loads policy rules — finds GEL-004 which allows APP_PIPELINE_SUBMIT
3. Generates an Execution Envelope with allowed operations
4. Checks the envelope permits APP_PIPELINE_SUBMIT
5. Builds Lane L1 context from all 5 VCKB documents
6. Logs everything to `logs/telemetry.jsonl`
7. Returns a structured PatternMap stub (FM1 needs API key to be real)

The `/gel/replay/:requestId` endpoint reconstructs and verifies that exact decision from the telemetry log alone.

